==English==
===Etymology===
From Persian ''p&aelig;'' (''leg'') and ''jama'' (''clothing'') (lit.: ''leg garment'') via [[Urdu]]/[[Hindi]].

===Noun===
'''pajamas''' ''plural''
#[[Clothes]] for wearing to bed and sleeping in, usually consisting of a loose-fitting shirt and pants.

